      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm looking at some digitized census records from Frederick County, Virginia, around the 1780s. I'm noticing some really weird spikes and drops in the population numbers between the 1770s and the 1790s that don't seem to align with the known patterns of westward expansion or the typical mortality rates from the era. Do you have any insight into what might cause such erratic fluctuations in these specific colonial records?",
